result.name: Tulsi Indian Restaurant

reviews.text: The place is not that easy to find (but Google maps is a big help). I found the food to be okay in terms of taste and quantity. They put less spices, probably in deference to the preferences of the HK customers. Service is good. The place is tiny. Quite congested. In my opinion, it is pretty expensive.
Taste was very good. Service was very quick. Ambiance was fine. Situated inside a small shopping complex, so you may have to search for it.
Best Indian restaurant in quarry bay area. The food is simply great and price is reasonable too.

Absolutely tasty! Vegetable soup is delish! Lamb masala amaze, garlin naan also a hit. Come for lunch and get a good priced set! Been two weeks in a row! If you don't like coriander don't come...or check first. Luckily I love it!

Absolutely Fantastic - lovely tender Lamb and a delicious vegetable curry alongside a Kashmiri Naan. 
Great cozy atmosphere, and incredible taste!

reviews.text: Taste is good and good price for lunch.

食物味道好好
咖哩有陣蕃茄味 唔太辣 好啱配烤餅同飯
推介芝士烤餅同芒果乳酪
Happy meal 1人餐 138蚊 夜晚食個價都算合理
Masala Tea 很香，羊扒一流👍，兩人套餐的份量很足，非常飽足^^
平日有餐，個combo可以試唔同食物，唔算辣但惹味，70蚊算唔錯。
